<DOCNO> APW19990402.0070 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 16:21:51 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Pisciotta Gets Braves Triple-A Deal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Braves on Friday signed free agent  
right-hander Marc Pisciotta to a contract with Triple-A Richmond. 
</P>
<P>
	Pisciotta, 28, was 1-2 with a 4.09 ERA in 43 games for the  
Chicago Cubs last season. He was 2-2 with a 7.16 ERA in eight 
spring outings for the Cubs before his release on Tuesday. 
</P>
<P>
	Pisciotta, from Marietta, Ga., who pitched at Georgia Tech, was  
a 19th round selection by the Pittsburgh Pirates in the 1991 
amateur draft. He has a 4-3 record with 3.73 ERA in 67 major league 
games. 
</P>
</TEXT>
