<HEADLINE> Woman Charged in Killing Newborn </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HIALEAH, Fla. (AP) -- A woman at a state-licensed home for adults  
with mental and physical disabilities heard her newborn cry before 
she tried to flush him down the toilet, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Daisy McFadden, 34, was charged today with first-degree murder a  
day after her son was found in the toilet at Adam Home, an 
assisted-living community just northwest of Miami. 
</P>
<P>
	An employee had noticed a trail of blood and followed it to Ms.  
McFadden's room, police said. 
</P>
<P>
	Employees at the home were aware that Ms. McFadden was pregnant,  
said Lt. Jerry Freeman. He said he had no information about the 
identity of the baby's father. 
</P>
<P>
	The medical examiner concluded that the baby was alive when born  
and died as a result of being submerged in the water. He was 
between 32 weeks and 34 weeks old and weighed only 4.2 pounds. 
</P>
<P>
	``Ms. McFadden had told people the baby cried after it was born  
and before it went in the water,'' said Lt. Jerry Freeman. ``The 
baby showed some trauma to the head. There was some evidence that 
suggested she may have had it on the toilet.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Ms. McFadden's roommate, who was sleeping during the birth, also  
said she heard the baby cry, Freeman said. 
</P>
<P>
	Freeman said he did not know the specifics of Ms. McFadden's  
disability, who was recovering at a nearby hospital. She was 
expected to be transferred to a hospital detention area under 
control of state prison officials. She also will undergo a mental 
evaluation, Freeman said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
