<DOCNO> APW19990402.0105 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 07:05:04 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> financial </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Portmans Agree To Settle Suits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- Architect-developer John C. Portman Jr. and his  
son have reportedly agreed to settle two sexual harassment suits. 
</P>
<P>
	``I got the word that they had worked both cases out,'' Judge  
John R. Strother Jr. of U.S. District Court told The Atlanta 
Journal-Constitution on Thursday. ``...They are going to send some 
papers in to the court next week.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Last year, two former employees filed the lawsuits, which also  
targeted AMC Inc., the Portman firm that operates the downtown 
trade market complex. 
</P>
<P>
	Stacey Schoppenhorst and Masa Kisner alleged they were subjected  
to ongoing verbal and physical harassment during their employment 
by AMC and that the company allowed a climate of sexual harassment. 
</P>
<P>
	The Journal-Constitution said neither the attorney for the women  
nor the attorneys for Jeffrey Portman or AMC responded Thursday to 
phone inquiries about the settlement. John Portman's attorney could 
not be reached, it said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
