<HEADLINE> Mighty Ducks 4, Rangers 1 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	NEW YORK (AP) -- Teemu Selanne scored two goals to increase his  
NHL-leading total to 45 as the Anaheim Mighty Ducks beat the New 
York Rangers 4-1 Friday night. 
</P>
<P>
	The loss was another blow to the Rangers' fading playoff hopes.  
New York trails Boston by seven points for the Eastern Conference's 
final playoff spot, with seven games left for the Rangers and eight 
for the Bruins. 
</P>
<P>
	Anaheim took a 1-0 lead 2:28 into the game when Selanne  
intercepted a pass by Brian Leetch for a breakaway and beat goalie 
Mike Richter with a slapshot from outside the blue line. 
</P>
<P>
	Travis Green put the Ducks ahead 2-0 with his 13th goal of the  
season at 6:43 when he took a trailing pass from Pavel Trnka on a 
three-on-one break and beat Richter high to the far side. 
</P>
<P>
	Kevin Stevens made it 2-1 at 10:07 with his 22nd goal of the  
season. Stevens took a hard slapshot from the blue line that goalie 
Guy Hebert couldn't handle. 
</P>
<P>
	Selanne gave the Ducks a 3-1 lead with a power-play goal at  
10:09 of the second period, one-timing a pass from Paul Kariya into 
the net. 
</P>
<P>
	Selanne returned the favor at 16:41 of the second period,  
feeding Kariya during a four-on-four for his 35th goal of the 
season. 
</P>
<P>
	Rangers center Petr Nedved, hindered by a strained ribcage  
muscle, played only 64 seconds over two first-period shifts and did 
not return to the ice. 
</P>
</TEXT>
