<DOCNO> APW19990402.0121 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1999-04-02 00:42:16 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<CATEGORY> usa </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Barbara Bush Has Back Surgery </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOUSTON (AP) -- Former first lady Barbara Bush was released from  
a hospital, one day after undergoing back surgery. 
</P>
<P>
	``It went very, very well. She's up walking around,'' former  
President George Bush said Thursday outside of Methodist Hospital. 
``The doctor's happy with it, and I'm happy with it. The doctors 
took wonderful care of her.'' 
</P>
<P>
	He declined to elaborate on his wife's condition, as did  
hospital officials. 
</P>
<P>
	A spokesman said Mrs. Bush, 73, had wanted to keep the operation  
quiet, but her husband made reference to the surgery Wednesday 
during a fund-raiser. 
</P>
</TEXT>
