<HEADLINE> The Money's On Sosa and McGwire </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	LAS VEGAS (AP) -- Like Mark McGwire's chances of hitting at least  
61 home runs this season? 
</P>
<P>
	You can bet on it at several Las Vegas sports books, who figure  
both McGwire and Sammy Sosa will have big home run years once 
again. 
</P>
<P>
	At the Las Vegas Hilton, bettors can put money on whether the  
Cardinals' slugger will hit more or less than 60 1/2 home runs this 
season. Sammy Sosa's over-under total is 53 1/2. 
</P>
<P>
	Last season, McGwire broke the home run record with 70, while  
Sosa had 66. 
</P>
<P>
	McGwire is a 4-5 favorite at the Hilton to win the home run race  
again, while Sosa is close behind at 8-5. Albert Belle is 5-2, 
while Ken Griffey Jr. is 3-1. 
</P>
<P>
	At the Imperial Palace, Belle has generated the most action so  
far, according to assistant sports book manager Kelly Downey. 
</P>
<P>
	``There's been heavy betting on Belle,'' Downey said of the  
slugger now with the Baltimore Orioles. ``Everyone else's odds have 
gone up, while his have gone down.'' 
</P>
<P>
	Bettors can also wager on other baseball propositions, including  
Randy Johnson's chances to lead the majors in strikeouts (2-1) and 
Los Angeles Dodgers reliever Jeff Shaw as the favorite for most 
saves (7-2). 
</P>
</TEXT>
