<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Excellent Meeting Wins in Arkansas </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	HOT SPRINGS, Ark. (AP) -- Excellent Meeting took the lead on the  
turn and defeated The Happy Hopper by 2 1/2 lengths in the $250,000 
Fantasy Stakes at Oaklawn Park on Friday. 
</P>
<P>
	It was the fourth straight victory for the Bob Baffert-trained  
Excellent Meeting and her seventh in her last eight starts. Her 
only defeat during that time was by a half-length to 
Silverbulletday in the Breeder's Cup Juvenile Fillies. 
</P>
<P>
	Owned by Golden Eagle Farm, Excellent Meeting has been mentioned  
by Baffert as a Kentucky Derby possibility. 
</P>
<P>
	Ridden by Kent Desormeaux, Excellent Meeting covered 1 1-16  
miles in 1:42 3-5. 
</P>
<P>
	The favorite in a field of six returned $2.60, $2.40, $2.20. The  
Happy Hopper paid $3.60 and $2.20. Dreams Gallore was worth $2.20. 
</P>
<P>
	Excellent Meeting went by The Happy Hopper in the far turn and  
quickly opened daylight. Desormeaux whipped her five times on the 
right hip, glanced toward the rail at The Happy Hopper and popped 
his mount one more time for good measure. 
</P>
<P>
	Excellent Meeting had four firsts, three seconds and a third in  
eight starts as a 2-year-old. After the Breeders' Cup Juvenile 
Fillies, she came back with an eight-length victory in a stakes 
race at Hollywood Park. After a two-month layoff, she captured the 
Las Virgenes Stakes by four lengths. A month later, she was a neck 
winner in the Santa Anita Oaks. 
</P>
</TEXT>
