<CATEGORY> sports </CATEGORY>
<HEADLINE> Hawks' Steve Smith on Injured List </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ATLANTA (AP) -- The Atlanta Hawks placed guard Steve Smith on the  
injured list Friday because of a sprained left knee. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith injured the knee Thursday in a second-quarter collision  
with New Jersey Nets forward Keith Van Horn. 
</P>
<P>
	Smith will likely be out of action 7-10 days, Hawks spokesman  
Arthur Triche said. However, the Hawks chose not to replace Smith 
on the roster, meaning he won't have to sit out the mandatory five 
games if he recovers early. 
</P>
<P>
	An MRI scan of Smith's knee Friday revealed no swelling, Triche  
said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
