<HEADLINE> Amtrak Train Rams Car, Killing One </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	WEST PALM BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- An Amtrak train slammed into a car  
that had been pushed in its path, killing a passenger. Five people 
were injured. 
</P>
<P>
	No injuries were reported among the train passengers or crew in  
Thursday night's collision. The train was heading to Miami from New 
York. 
</P>
<P>
	The car had stopped for flashing lights at the crossing when  
another car rammed it from behind, spinning the vehicle onto the 
tracks, where it stalled, according to the Florida Highway Patrol. 
</P>
<P>
	Jennifer Fuente, the 18-year-old who was killed, couldn't free  
herself from the car's back seat before the train slammed into the 
car, pushing it about more than a quarter-mile down the tracks. Two 
other people in her car were injured. 
</P>
<P>
	The second car continued across the tracks and through the  
crossing. Three people in that car suffered minor injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	No tickets were issued, but the investigation was not complete.  
</P>
</TEXT>
