<HEADLINE> Dead Transvestite's Boyfriend Sought </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	ABBEVILLE, Ga. (AP) -- A transvestite fatally beaten on a rural  
Georgia road told investigators before he died that his boyfriend 
was responsible for the attack, the sheriff said. 
</P>
<P>
	Tracey Thompson, 33, who often hitchhiked up and down Interstate  
75 in Georgia and Florida dressed as a woman, died in a hospital 
Tuesday from his injuries. 
</P>
<P>
	``He was pretty much falling in and out of consciousness,''  
Sheriff Stacy Bloodsworth said Thursday. ``He said his boyfriend 
had beaten him.'' Thompson did not identify the boyfriend by name, 
investigators said. 
</P>
<P>
	Authorities said they don't know how or why Thompson ended up on  
a country road 10 miles east of I-75 where he was beaten with a 
baseball bat. 
</P>
<P>
	The Georgia Bureau of Investigation has been reviewing the case  
as a possibly hate-motivated crime. 
</P>
<P>
	``We don't know whether or not this had anything to do with his  
lifestyle,'' said Gary Rothwell of the agency. 
</P>
<P>
	No arrests have been made in the case.  
</P>
